.TH "sparse_keymap_setup" 9 "sparse_keymap_setup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sparse_keymap_setup \- set up sparse keymap for an input device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sparse_keymap_setup
.BI "(struct input_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct key_entry *keymap "  ","
.BI "int (*setup)(struct input_dev *, struct key_entry *) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Input device
.IP "keymap" 12
Keymap in form of array of \fIkey_entry\fP structures ending
with KE_END type entry
.IP "setup" 12
Function that can be used to adjust keymap entries
depending on device's needs, may be NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function calculates size and allocates copy of the original
keymap after which sets up input device event bits appropriately.
The allocated copy of the keymap is automatically freed when it
is no longer needed.
